<!-- ── CHAPTERS ── -->
<div class="l-chapters">

  <!-- Ch 01: The Dataset -->
  <div class="l-chapter">
    <div class="l-ch-text" data-reveal>
      <span class="l-ch-num">01 / 03 — THE DATASET</span>
      <h2 class="l-ch-head">205 people.<br><span class="l-serif-italic">Real diagnosis. Real keystrokes.</span></h2>
      <p class="l-ch-body">
        The TAPPY dataset collected longitudinal keystroke recordings from participants with and without Parkinson's disease over 12 months. Each session captured raw keydown and keyup timestamps at millisecond precision — the same resolution Cadence uses on you.
      </p>
      <p class="l-ch-body" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
        From those recordings, researchers extracted timing biomarkers that correlate with motor-cognitive coupling — the loop between your brain's executive planning centers and your fingers. Cadence learned its risk weights from this corpus.
      </p>
      <div class="l-ch-tags">
        <span class="l-ch-tag">TAPPY corpus</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">205 participants</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Parkinson's / Healthy</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Longitudinal · 12 months</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="l-ch-visual">
      <canvas id="ch-dataset-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Ch 02: The Features -->
  <div class="l-chapter">
    <div class="l-ch-visual">
      <canvas id="ch-features-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
    <div class="l-ch-text" data-reveal>
      <span class="l-ch-num">02 / 03 — THE FEATURES</span>
      <h2 class="l-ch-head">Seven signals your<br><span class="l-serif-italic">fingers reveal.</span></h2>
      <p class="l-ch-body">
        No two features measure the same thing. Mean inter-key interval captures raw speed; its standard deviation captures <em>consistency</em> — the metric that diverges earliest in cognitive decline. Hold time isolates how long each key is depressed; flight time measures the gap between releasing one key and pressing the next.
      </p>
      <p class="l-ch-body" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
        Backspace rate tracks correction tendency. Pause frequency counts hesitations longer than 500ms. Together they form a 7-dimensional fingerprint that changes in ways you cannot consciously control.
      </p>
      <div class="l-ch-tags">
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Mean IKI</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">IKI std dev</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Hold time</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Flight time</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">WPM</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Backspace rate</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Pause freq</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Ch 03: The Model -->
  <div class="l-chapter">
    <div class="l-ch-text" data-reveal>
      <span class="l-ch-num">03 / 03 — THE MODEL</span>
      <h2 class="l-ch-head">Sigmoid scoring,<br><span class="l-serif-italic">calibrated on evidence.</span></h2>
      <p class="l-ch-body">
        Cadence's inference engine computes a weighted sum of your z-scored features, then maps it through a sigmoid function to produce a risk score between 0 and 1. The weights were derived from the TAPPY feature importances; the thresholds (Low &lt; 0.33, Medium &lt; 0.55, High ≥ 0.55) were calibrated against clinical labels in the corpus.
      </p>
      <p class="l-ch-body" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
        Because every computation runs in Node.js at submission time, there's no Python runtime dependency in production — the model is a 512-byte JSON file of weights and scalers, fast enough to score any session in under 1ms.
      </p>
      <div class="l-ch-tags">
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Sigmoid activation</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">model.json weights</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">Low · Medium · High</span>
        <span class="l-ch-tag">&lt; 1ms inference</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="l-ch-visual">
      <canvas id="ch-model-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

